🧩 **yarn build OHIF has a Webpack Ternserplugin call. On a machine with limited memory sometimes it sends a SIGKILL with the final error: not enough memory. Are there any minimum memory requirements for an application that runs OHIF that a server should have maybe to minimize any ram swaps and just have a clean build.**

* **Root cause**

  * Webpack’s **TerserPlugin (minification step)** is memory intensive
  * On low-memory machines:

    * Process can be killed (SIGKILL)
    * Typically occurs near the end of the build
* **Build-time vs runtime**

  * This is primarily a **build-time issue**, not runtime viewer performance
* **Mitigation strategies**

  * Increase available system memory (RAM)
  * Adjust Node.js memory limits (e.g., `--max-old-space-size`)
  * Reduce build parallelism if applicable
  * Run builds on machines with more resources (CI/CD or cloud)
* **General guidance**

  * No strict minimum defined, but:

    * Low-memory environments are prone to failure during minification
    * Stable builds typically require sufficient headroom to avoid swapping

